## Development rules

1. Keep code simple and clean — no dead code
2. Commit after every meaningful progress
3. Write thorough tests — run with `[test command]`
4. Do not stop to ask for confirmation — the user is not at the keyboard
5. Maintain a work-in-progress log in IMPLEMENTATION_NOTES.md
6. Re-read this file after every context compaction
7. No additional dependencies without explicit approval
8. No marginal improvements (<1%) that add complexity
9. Never commit unrelated/unstaged files
10. Read source-of-truth files before modifying
11. Keep this file aligned with the actual workflow and tests
12. Update README.md if CLI/runtime behavior changes
13. Do not access the internet without explicit permission
14. Comment code only where the logic is not self-evident
15. All project artifacts in English (AGENTS.md, SPEC.md, comments, commit messages)

